2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funama.unmissions.org%2Funama-deeply-concerned-over-detentions-afghan-women-and-girls-0%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20UNAMA%20report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNAMA%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0states%20that%2C%20in%20one%20instance%2C%20a%20woman%20was%20advised%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9CMinistry%20for%20the%20Propagation%20of%20Virtue%E2%80%9D%20to%20get%20married%C2%A0to%20keep%20her%20job%20at%20a%20healthcare%20facility.%20The%20ministry%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20improper%20for%20an%20unmarried%20woman%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20just%20a%20few%20examples%20of%20many%2C%20says%20Zahra%20Nader.%20Nader%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20online%20magazine%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzantimes.com%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20Zan%20Times%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EZan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20started%20it%20in%20August%202022%20to%20give%20girls%20and%20women%20in%20her%20homeland%20a%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20working%20under%20the%20Taliban%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENader%2C%2034%2C%20lives%20in%20Canada.%20When%20she%20flew%20from%20Kabul%20to%20Toronto%20to%20start%20her%20PhD%20in%20gender%20studies%20at%20York%20University%2C%20the%20Taliban%20were%20not%20in%20power.%20Under%20their%20rule%2C%20it%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20possible%20for%20her%20to%20travel%20abroad%20to%20continue%20her%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20I%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20support%20girls%20and%20women%20in%20my%20homeland%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20stresses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20she%20left%20Afghanistan%2C%20Nader%20worked%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20reporting%20for%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20among%20others.%20Today%2C%20she%20is%20still%20in%20touch%20with%20female%20colleagues%20who%20have%20either%20lost%20their%20jobs%20since%20the%20Taliban%20seized%20power%20or%20even%20had%20to%20flee%20the%20country%2C%20fearing%20for%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20our%20magazine%C2%A0%3Cem%3EZan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Afghan%20women%20journalists%20work%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20the%20country%2C%20reporting%20in%20Farsi%20and%20English%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nader.%20%E2%80%9CA%20small%20group%20of%20women%20journalists%20in%20Afghanistan%20collects%20local%20information.%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%20dangerous%20for%20them%20to%20work%2C%20and%20they%20report%20on%20topics%20the%20Taliban%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20hear%20about%3A%20LGBTQ%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20human%20rights%2C%20domestic%20violence%2C%20or%20child%20marriage.%20There%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhow-the-taliban-are-violating-womens-rights-in-afghanistan%2Fa-66143514%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20to%20report%20on%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20lot%20of%20injustice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarsi%20is%20related%20to%20Afghanistan%E2%80%99s%20official%20language%2C%20Dari%2C%20and%20is%20understood%20in%20most%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20they%20seized%20power%20in%20August%202021%2C%20the%20Taliban%20banished%20women%20from%20almost%20all%20areas%20of%20public%20life.%20Girls%20were%20banned%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafghanistantaliban-increase-crackdown-on-girls-education%2Fa-67257146%5C%22%3Eattending%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0beyond%20sixth%20grade.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafghan-women-rally-against-talibans-beauty-salon-ban%2Fa-66285084%5C%22%3EBeauty%20salons%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20closed%20down.%20In%20a%20decree%20issued%20in%20May%202022%2C%20women%20were%20advised%20to%20wear%20a%20full-body%20burqa%20that%20showed%20only%20their%20eyes.%20Anyone%20who%20dares%20to%20leave%20the%20house%20without%20a%20full-body%20burqa%20is%20beaten%20on%20the%20street%20and%20taken%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20families%20see%20it%20as%20deeply%20shameful%20if%20the%20Taliban%20take%20away%20a%20female%20family%20member.%20So%20many%20fathers%20and%20husbands%20forbid%20their%20daughters%20and%20wives%20to%20leave%20the%20house%2C%E2%80%9D%20Zahra%20Nader%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCritical%20reporting%2C%20and%20anything%20that%20contradicts%20Taliban%20propaganda%2C%20is%20extremely%20dangerous.%20Our%20local%20colleagues%20have%20to%20be%20extremely%20careful.%20They%20write%20under%20pseudonyms%C2%A0and%C2%A0only%20leave%20the%20house%20in%20consultation%20with%20us.%20These%20women%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20each%20other%20and%20only%20have%20contact%20with%20colleagues%20abroad.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EActions%2C%20not%20words%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENader%20initially%20used%20her%20own%20savings%20to%20set%20up%20the%20online%20magazine.%20She%20and%20her%20colleagues%20sometimes%20also%20worked%20without%20pay.%20Almost%2018%20months%20later%2C%20they%20now%20receive%20scholarships%2C%20grants%2C%20and%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20to%20enlighten%20people.%20We%20advocate%20for%20critical%20thinking%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Zahra%20Nader.%20%E2%80%9COur%20readers%20are%20mainly%20women%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20but%20we%20also%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20hits%20from%20other%20countries%20where%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20refugees%20from%20Afghanistan.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20of%20her%20fellow%20Afghans%2C%20Zahra%20Nader%20is%20counting%20on%20the%20international%20community%E2%80%99s%20solidarity%20and%20political%20support%20for%20women%20and%20girls%20in%20her%20homeland.%20Countries%20that%20were%20involved%20in%20Afghanistan%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years%20and%20that%20promote%20a%20feminist%20foreign%20policy%20should%20campaign%20for%20women%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20their%20rights%2C%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20just%20mean%20giving%20speeches%20or%20condemning%20the%20Taliban.%20That%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20accomplish%20anything.%20The%20Taliban%20must%20see%20actions.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20should%20be%20sanctioned%20and%20unable%20to%20travel%20until%20they%20change%20their%20misogynistic%20policies%20and%20allow%20women%20actively%20to%20participate%20in%20public%20life%20again.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafghanistan-an-online-magazine-for-women%2Fa-68067604%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706187876000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F23150336%2FTaliban-humvee.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdefying-repressive-taliban-regime-afghan-women-run-digital-magazine-with-critical-reporting%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Afghan%20women%20are%20advocating%20for%20their%20rights%20under%20the%20rule%20of%20the%20radical%20Taliban%20through%20an%20online%20magazine%2C%20Zan%20Times%2C%20published%20by%20a%20group%20of%20female%20Afghan%20journalists.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdefying-repressive-taliban-regime-afghan-women-run-digital-magazine-with-critical-reporting%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taiwan%20president-elect%20says%20he%20hopes%20for%20continued%20firm%20US%20support%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706187836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107150283%2Cimgsize-1101304.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-wor