Cp%3EWe%20continued%20to%20some%20of%20his%20old%20schools%20when%2C%20alas%2C%20we%20ended%20at%20The%20Luber%2C%20the%20last%20place%20he%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20took%20in%20a%20border%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20room%2C%20he%20said%20pointing%20at%20the%20window.%20It%20was%20hard%20to%20imagine%20growing%20up%20in%20that%20large%20Victorian%20home%20where%20he%20would%20have%20had%20such%20little%20space.%20He%20didn't%20seem%20to%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ended%20our%20visit%20with%20a%20luxurious%20lunch%20at%20a%20noted%20restaurant%20on%20Arthur%20Avenue.%20We%20shared%20a%20meal.%20Drank%20some%20wine%2C%20and%20he%20even%20paid.%20That%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rarest%20things%20of%20all.%20I%20mean%2C%20he%20did%20grow%20up%20in%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20after%20all.%20Money%20is%20not%20something%20he%20will%20ever%20take%20lightly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20certain%20what%20has%20kept%20him%20so%20spry%20all%20these%20years%20later.%20Maybe%20it%20was%20the%20growing%20up%20in%20the%20Boogie%20Down%20Bronx%2C%20having%20to%20work%20for%20everything%2C%20always%20using%20his%20hands%2C%20his%20love%20of%20tennis.%20I%20am%20not%20sure%20if%20it%20is%20purely%20genetic.%20But%20I%20know%20that%20even%20though%20he%20has%20technically%20gotten%20older%2C%20he%20shows%20little%20signs%20of%20aging.%20His%20father%20was%20the%20same%20way.%20I%20hope%20that%2C%20too%2C%20will%20be%20my%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnonagenarian-dad-memory-sharp-aging-longevity-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706186701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b12dfe6c8f0a134f7991f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnonagenarian-dad-memory-sharp-aging-longevity-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%2091-year-old%20dad%20still%20travels%20solo%