C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20millennial%20tech%20worker%20earned%20over%20%24500%2C000%20across%20four%20jobs%20in%202022.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecretly%20working%20multiple%20remote%20jobs%20at%20once%20made%20an%20%26quot%3Bincredible%20difference%26quot%3B%20to%20his%20finances.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20gave%20up%20his%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-workers-secret-two-multiple-jobs-salaries-tech-tips-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eoveremployment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%20last%20year%20after%20burning%20out.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%2C%20a%20Texas-based%20tech%20worker%20in%20his%2030s%2C%20first%20learned%20about%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-full-time-tech-layoffs-work-retirement-savings-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoveremployed%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20community%20on%20Reddit.%20He%20thought%20the%20idea%20of%20secretly%20working%20multiple%20remote%20jobs%20to%20boost%20his%20income%20sounded%20appealing%2C%20so%20he%20decided%20to%20see%20if%20it%20was%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20William%20technically%20had%20two%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20corporate%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecustomer-facing%20tech%20role%20and%20running%20his%20remote%20consulting%20business.%20But%20that%20June%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20leave%20his%20corporate%20role%20and%20take%20on%20two%20new%20jobs%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-full-time-tech-productivity-work-retirement-savings-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elarge%20tech%20companies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20starting%20both%20within%20a%20week%20of%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20while%20continuing%20to%20run%20his%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20he'd%20earned%20over%20%24500%2C000%20across%20the%20four%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20which%20reflects%20his%20combined%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-calculate-annual-income%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egross%20earnings%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20any%20withholdings%2C%20like%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20documents%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20said%20swapping%20one%20corporate%20job%20for%20two%20more%20than%20doubled%20his%20annual%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20is%20among%20a%20niche%20group%20of%20workers%20across%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20them%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-retirement-worker-tech-career-savings-productivity-home-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etech%20industry%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20who%20have%20secretly%20held%20multiple%20remote%20jobs.%20Working%20more%20than%20one%20job%20at%20once%20may%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoonlighting-working-two-remote-jobs-legal-financial-freedom-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eviolate%20federal%20or%20state%20laws%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20it%20could%20breach%20some%20employment%20contracts%20and%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-viral-linkedin-post-engineers-working-two-jobs-overemployment-theft-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efireable%20offense%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20a%20worker%20is%20ever%20found%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20made%20an%20incredible%20difference%20for%20my%20finances%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20William%2C%20whose%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20BI%20but%20has%20been%20withheld%20due%20to%20his%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20able%20to%20pay%20off%20any%20outstanding%20student%20loan%20debt%2C%20eliminate%20debts%20on%20my%20wife's%20side%2C%20and%20throw%20some%20significant%20investment%20into%20my%20own%20ventures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extra%20income%20was%20valuable%20for%20William%20as%20he%20grew%20his%20business%2C%20which%20he%20said%20lost%20roughly%20%24100%2C000%20in%202022%20due%20to%20investments%20he%20made%20into%20it.%20He%20said%20overemployment%20also%20provided%20him%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Blarge%20safety%20net%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20became%20especially%20important%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-laid-off-every-day-january-recession-downturn-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elayoffs%20started%20to%20spread%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20February%202023%2C%20only%20eight%20months%20after%20he%20started%2C%20William%20decided%20he%20was%20burned%20out%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20overemployed%20any%20longer.%20That%20month%2C%20he%20resigned%20from%20both%20of%20his%20corporate%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOveremployment%20proved%20to%20be%20unsustainable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20started%20the%20two%20corporate%20roles%2C%20William%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bconstantly%26quot%3B%20receiving%20messages%20from%20recruiters%20about%20new%20opportunities.%20To%20keep%20his%20interviewing%20skills%20sharp%20%E2%80%94%20and%20see%20what%20companies%20had%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%94%20he%20explored%20several%20of%20these%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20his%20peak%2C%20William%20said%20he%20had%20as%20many%20as%20six%20job%20offers%20lined%20up%2C%20many%20of%20which%20offered%20over%20%24300%2C000%20in%20total%20annual%20compensation.%20After%20thinking%20it%20over%2C%20he%20accepted%20the%20two%20corporate%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20keeping%20his%20overemployment%20a%20secret%20from%20everyone%20outside%20his%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20William's%20typical%20weekday%2C%20he%20worked%20on%20his%20business%20from%207%20a.m.%20to%209%20a.m.%2C%20juggled%20both%20corporate%20jobs%20from%209%20a.m.%20to%205%20p.m.%2C%20and%20then%20focused%20on%20his%20business%20again%20from%205%20p.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20was%20able%20to%20balance%20the%20corporate%20jobs%20because%20he%20was%20very%20productive%20and%20both%20roles%20rewarded%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20more%20so%20than%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20juggling%20multiple%20roles%20proved%20to%20be%20possible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20financially%20lucrative%20%E2%80%94%20William%20said%20overemployment%20began%20to%20take%20a%20toll.%20He%20found%20himself%20thinking%20about%20his%20jobs%20even%20when%20he%20wasn't%20working%20%E2%80%94%20leaving%20him%20little%20time%20to%20relax%20%E2%80%94%20and%20said%20his%20household%20responsibilities%20began%20to%20pile%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20end%20up%20getting%20burned%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20quitting%20both%20jobs%20last%20year%20allowed%20him%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20his%20family%2C%20travel%2C%20and%20focus%20on%20his%20consulting%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChecking%20company%20policies%20and%20avoiding%20meeting%20conflicts%20can%20help%20job%20jugglers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20his%20overemployed%20stint%20was%20fairly%20brief%2C%20William%20said%20he%20learned%20a%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20including%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20get%20away%20with%20job%20juggling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20workers%20should%20check%20if%20a%20company%20has%20an%20explicit%20policy%20against%20employees%20having%20multiple%20jobs.%20William%20said%20both%20of%20his%20companies%20allowed%20employees%20to%20have%20multiple%20jobs%20as%20long%20as%20they%20could%20meet%20expectations%20and%20there%20were%20no%20direct%20conflicts%20of%20interest%2C%20such%20as%20working%20