%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22scotland%20google%20maps%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e7f39e7c6a200018428117%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20showing%20Scotland%20in%20the%20UK.%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Maps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Scotland%2C%20a%20small%20country%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20with%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrscotland.gov.uk%2Fstatistics-and-data%2Fstatistics%2Fscotlands-facts%2Fpopulation-of-scotland%5C%22%3E5.4%20million%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Records%20of%20Scotland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Scotland%20is%20part%20of%20the%20UK%2C%20there%20are%20traditions%20that%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20that%20aren't%20celebrated%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20nation%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20lived%20in%20the%20country%20for%20most%20of%20my%20life%2C%20except%20for%20a%20short%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrit-semester-abroad-pennsylvania-us-college-culture-2022-1%5C%22%3Estudy-abroad%20semester%20in%20Pennsylvania%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%2C%20and%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20I%20have%20spent%20time%20in%20London%20for%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20when%20I%20made%20friends%20who%20weren't%20from%20Scotland%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20my%20US%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20that%20I%20realized%20just%20how%20unique%20some%20of%20our%20traditions%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEvery%20January%2C%20we%20celebrate%20Burns%20Night%20in%20honor%20of%20the%20famous%20poet%20Robert%20Burns.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22robert%20burns%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80cc804ce6e0018d7b0c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222593%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20Burns.%3Cp%3EKean%20Collection%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBurns%20Night%20falls%20on%20January%2025%20every%20year%20in%20honor%20of%20Robert%20Burns%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BRabbie%20Burns%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he's%20known%20in%20Scotland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurns%20was%20an%2018th-century%20poet%20from%20Dumfries%20and%20is%20considered%20the%20country's%20national%20poet.%20He's%20best%20known%20for%20writing%20the%20lyrics%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FAuld-Lang-Syne%5C%22%3EAuld%20Lang%20Syne%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20song%20often%20performed%20on%20New%20Year's%20Eve%20in%20Scotland%20and%20in%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20in%20elementary%20school%2C%20our%20teachers%20used%20Burns%20Night%20to%20teach%20us%20about%20poetry.%20I%20remember%20performing%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Burns%20Factor%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20competition%20in%20which%20we%20had%20to%20recite%20our%20favorite%20Burns%20poem%20by%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOn%20Burns%20Night%2C%20we%20eat%20a%20traditional%20Scottish%20meal%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BBurns%20Supper.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22burns%20supper%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80d9c04ce6e0018d7b0e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHaggis%2C%20neeps%2C%20and%20tatties.%3Cp%3EColin%20McPherson%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Burns%20Night%2C%20many%20families%20across%20Scotland%20enjoy%20a%20%26quot%3BBurns%20Supper%26quot%3B%20for%20their%20dinner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Burns%20Supper%20consists%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaking-traditional-haggis-scotland-macsween-edinburgh-2020-4%5C%22%3Ehaggis%3C%2Fa%3E%20(spiced%20meat%20encased%20in%20animal%20intestines)%2C%20neeps%20(turnips)%2C%20and%20tatties%20(potatoes).%20While%20it's%20most%20popular%20on%20Burns%20Night%2C%20my%20family%20eats%20haggis%20several%20times%20a%20year%2C%20and%20it%20can%20usually%20be%20found%20served%20at%20restaurants%20any%20time%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20might%20also%20choose%20to%20have%20a%20Burns%20Supper%20on%20St.%20Andrew's%20Day%2C%20Scotland's%20national%20day%2C%20which%20falls%20on%20November%2030%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20haggis%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-foods-america-banned-2017-7%5C%22%3Ebanned%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%201971%20because%20the%20recipe%20includes%20sheep%20lung.%20But%20you%20can%20get%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finews.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fscotland%2Fvegetarian-haggis-rebranded-as-scottish-veggie-crumble-for-american-market-386985%5C%22%3Evegetarian%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20it%20in%20some%20stores%2C%20according%20to%20iNews%2C%20as%20well%20as%20versions%20that%20omit%20the%20banned%20ingredient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMen%20wear%20kilts%20at%20important%20celebrations%2C%20such%20as%20school%20proms%2C%20weddings%2C%20and%20graduations.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mikhaila's%20parents%20wedding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80c347c6a200018428403%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20of%20Mikhaila's%20parents%2C%20Debbie%20and%20David%20Friel%2C%20on%20their%20wedding%20day%20in%201995.%3Cp%3EMikhaila%20Friel%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKilts%20are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lochcarron.co.uk%2Fblog%2Fthe-history-of-the-kilt%2F%5C%22%3Etartan%20skirt-type%20garment%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20originated%20in%20the%20Scottish%20Highlands%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20according%20to%20Lochcarron%20of%20Scotland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20something%20men%20walk%20around%20in%20every%20day.%20Kilts%20are%20saved%20for%20special%20events%2C%20such%20as%20school%20proms%2C%20graduations%2C%20and%20weddings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20showed%20the%20above%20photo%20of%20my%20parents%20on%20their%20wedding%20day%20to%20some%20of%20my%20student%20friends%20in%20the%20US%2C%20they%20were%20surprised%20that%20my%20dad%20got%20married%20wearing%20a%20%26quot%3Bskirt.%26quot%3B%20But%20in%20Scotland%2C%20it's%20the%20norm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAt%20school%20dances%2C%20we%20don't%20dance%20to%20modern%20music.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20traditional%20Scottish%20dancing%2C%20known%20as%20ceilidhs.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ceilidh%20dance%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80eb57c6a20001842845c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20dance%20on%20the%20Royal%20Mile%20during%20the%20Hogmanay%20celebrations%20in%20Edinburgh.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Milligan%2FPA%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20ceilidh%20is%20a%20gathering%20that%20involves%20dancing%20to%20traditional%20folk%20music%2C%20either%20in%20partners%20or%20in%20groups%2C%20in%20choreographed%20routines%2C%20all%20of%20which%20have%20their%20own%20names.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20routines%20is%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DE7fikiE39Ws%5C%22%3EGay%20Gordons%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20our%20school%20threw%20a%20ceilidh%20every%20year%20before%20Christmas.%20For%20the%20full%20month%20of%20December%2C%20every%20gym%20class%20was%20dedicated%20to%20learning%20and%20practicing%20the%20different%20routines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20studied%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20had%20been%20years%20since%20I%20had%20been%20to%20a%20ceilidh%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20I%20still%20remembered%20every%20move%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BGay%20Gordons%26quot%3B%20and%20(unsuccessfully)%20attempted%20to%20teach%20it%20to%20my%20roommates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBagpipes%20are%20played%20at%20important%20events.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223632%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bagpiper%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80f937c6a200018428470%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBagpipe%20player%20at%20the%20Braemar%20Games%20in%20Scotland.%3Cp%3ETim%20Graham%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBagpipes%20are%20played%20at%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20events%2C%20including%20parades%2C%20weddings%2C%20funerals%2C%20and%20school%20assemblies.%20It's%20also%20common%20to%20see%20bagpipers%20busking%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Glasgow%20and%20Edinburgh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBagpipe%20music%20is%20popular%20in%20Scotland%2C%20and%20there%20are%20several%20piper%20bands%2C%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frhcp.scot%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%3ERed%20Hot%20Chilli%20Pipers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20have%20made%20a%20name%20for%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20the%20instrument's%20sometimes%20negative%20portrayal%20in%20pop%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Far_T1wlS_EY%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENew%20Year's%20Eve%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20Hogmanay%20in%20Scotland%20%E2%80%94%20involves%20several%20traditions.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22edinburgh%20new%20year's%20eve%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e80e007c6a200018428447%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFireworks%20in%20Edinburgh%20on%20New%20Year's%20Eve%202013.%3Cp%3ERoberto%20Ricciuti%2FRedferns%20via%20Ge