%20the%20lurid%20leviathan%20was%20indelible.%20But%20what%20is%20it%20an%20icon%20of%2C%20exactly%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELove%20them%20or%20loathe%20them%2C%20giant%20cruise%20ships%20are%20among%20the%20most%20remarkable%20success%20stories%20of%20the%20mass%20tourism%20age.%20In%20the%20mid-20th%20century%2C%20as%20commercial%20airplanes%20supplanted%20boats%20as%20the%20main%20mode%20of%20long-distance%20transportation%2C%20passenger%20shipping%20lines%20fell%20into%20steep%20decline.%20Cruising%20was%20initially%20a%20small-scale%20and%20ponderous%20pastime%3A%20Ships%20would%20dock%20at%20ports%20of%20call%20for%20several%20days%20and%20cater%20to%20a%20clientele%20that%20had%20both%20time%20and%20money.%20Then%20Ted%20Arison%2C%20the%20scion%20of%20an%20Israeli%20shipping%20family%2C%20flipped%20the%20industry%20on%20its%20head%20by%20asking%3A%20What%20if%20the%20boat%20itself%20was%20the%20destination%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%201972%2C%20Arison%20bought%20an%20old%20passenger%20liner%20and%20commissioned%20a%20hasty%20refit%20to%20provide%20space%20for%20onboard%20entertainment.%20Rechristened%20the%20Mardi%20Gras%2C%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-carnival-cruises-best-for-first-time-cruisers-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECarnival%20cruise%20ship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20sailed%20out%20of%20Miami%20that%20March.%20The%20modern%20cruising%20industry%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20cruising%20includes%20river%20cruises%2C%20luxury%20special-interest%20journeys%2C%20and%20monthslong%20expeditions%20to%20some%20of%20the%20most%20remote%20maritime%20environments%20in%20the%20world.%20But%20what%20most%20people%20think%20of%20are%20the%20massive%20ships%20that%20followed%20in%20the%20Mardi%20Gras'%20wake%3A%20a%20vacation%20on%20the%20water.%20A%20boat%20like%20the%20Icon%20will%20spend%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20its%20seven-day%20itinerary%20at%20sea%2C%20docking%20at%20only%20two%20or%20three%20ports%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20after%20the%20Mardi%20Gras'%20inaugural%20journey%2C%20the%20annual%20cruise-passenger%20load%20grew%20exponentially%20%E2%80%94%20from%20500%2C000%20in%201970%20to%20nearly%2030%20million%20in%202019.%20The%20Port%20of%20Miami%2C%20%26quot%3BCruise%20Capital%20of%20the%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20went%20from%20processing%2061%2C000%20passengers%20in%201950%20to%20nearly%2068%2C000%20passengers%20in%20a%20single%20day%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20expansion%20has%20pushed%20through%20some%20formidable%20bow%20waves.%20In%202012%2C%20the%20Costa%20Concordia%20made%20worldwide%20headlines%20when%20it%20foundered%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Tuscany%2C%20Italy%2C%20killing%2032%20people.%20Eight%20years%20later%2C%20cruise%20ships%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-diamond-princess-cruise-ship-coronavirus-quarantine-went-wrong-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDiamond%20Princess%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20early%20incubators%20for%20COVID-19.%20By%20summer%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarnival-corp-cruise-loses-billions-delta-variant-covid-19-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECarnival%20was%20hemorrhaging%20%241%20billion%20a%20month%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20borders%20reopened%2C%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20industry's%20recovery%20has%20been%20startling.%20Passenger%20numbers%20surged%20past%202019%20levels%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20week%2C%20in%20January%2C%20would%20typically%20be%20very%20quiet%2C%26quot%3B%20Aaron%20Saunders%2C%20a%20senior%20editor%20at%20the%20cruising-review%20site%20Cruise%20Critic%2C%20told%20me%20earlier%20this%20month.%20He%20was%20calling%20from%20the%20Golden%20Jubilee%20lounge%20of%20the%20Carnival%20Celebration%2C%20the%20largest%20vessel%20in%20Carnival's%20fleet%20(it%20has%20a%20roller%20coaster%20on%20deck).%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20ship%20is%20entirely%20sold%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20seen%20ships%20this%20consistently%20full.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20anyone%2C%20repeat%20cruisers%20have%20fueled%20the%20bounce%20back.%20In%20a%20December%202022%20survey%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcruising.org%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fclia-media%2Fresearch%2F2023%2F2023-clia-state-of-the-cruise-industry-report_low-res.ashx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECruise%20Lines%20International%20Association%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2085%25%20of%20passengers%20said%20that%20they%20would%20cruise%20again.%20The%20appeal%20was%20clear%3A%20In%20CLIA%20surveys%2C%20people%20said%20cruises%20were%20easier%20to%20arrange%2C%20more%20relaxing%2C%20and%20more%20%26quot%3Bpampering%26quot%3B%20than%20other%20holidays.%20People%20also%20coveted%20the%20variety%20of%20destinations%20and%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwenty%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20entertainment%20was%20extremely%20limited%20compared%20to%20what%20you%20have%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Sue%20Bryant%2C%20a%20veteran%20cruise%20journalist%20and%20editor%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20first%20ship%20introduced%20a%20climbing%20wall%2C%20it%20was%20considered%20outrageously%20revolutionary.%20Now%20you've%20got%20zip%20lines%2C%20water%20slides%2C%20and%20musical%20shows%20from%20Broadway%20and%20the%20West%20End.%20The%20product%20is%20always%20improving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20the%20most%20surprising%20feature%20of%20this%20surging%20popularity%20is%20how%20much%20of%20it%20is%20also%20being%20driven%20by%20younger%20travelers.%20Data%20recently%20compiled%20by%20researchers%20at%20CivicScience%20showed%20that%2069%25%20of%2018-%20to%2024-year-olds%20were%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20interested%26quot%3B%20in%20going%20on%20a%20cruise%2C%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20any%20age%20group.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20videos%20of%20life%20aboard%20another%20Royal%20Caribbean%20ship%2C%20the%20Serenade%20of%20the%20Seas%2C%20six%20weeks%20into%20a%20nine-month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-royal-caribbeans-9-month-ultimate-world-cruise-unusual-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUltimate%20World%20Cruise%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20had%20become%20a%20viral%20sensation.%20Posts%20with%20the%20hashtag%20%23ultimateworldcruise%2C%20most%20of%20them%20created%20by%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20influencers%2C%20had%20accrued%20over%20350%20million%20views%20on%20TikTok%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20industry%20casts%20off%20outdated%20clich%C3%A9s%20of%20retirees%2C%20shuffleboard%2C%20and%20black-tie%20dining%2C%20some%20companies%20have%20gone%20all%20out%20for%20the%20young-adult%20market.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirgin-voyages-sea-terrace-room-balcony-photo-cruise-cabin-tour-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EVirgin%20Voyages%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20debuted%20in%202021%20with%20the%20promise%20to%20%26quot%3Bsail%20our%20ships%20with%20sass%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20a%20no-kids%20policy%20and%20boasts%20onboard%20amenities%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20brunch%20bars%2C%20Peloton%20classes%2C%20and%20resident%20drag%20performers%20%E2%80%94%20tailored%20to%20a%20young%20customer%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20think%20that%20cruises%20are%20all%20about%20partying.%20Others%20have%20an%20idea%20that%20cruises%20are%20formal%2C%20all%20about%20ballroom%20dancing%2C%26quot%3B%20Emma%20Le%20Teace%2C%20a%20cruise%20writer%20and%20YouTuber%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20these%20options%20do%20exist.%20But%20young%20customers%20are%20realizing%20that%20there%20are%20hundreds%20of%20options%20in%20between.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20in%20a%20period%20of%20high%20inflation%2C%20all%20these%20perceived%20upsides%20are%20available%20for%20controlled%20costs.%20The%20standard%20cruise%20package%20is%20all-inclusive.%20Though%20alcohol%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-ways-save-money-on-cruise-from-frequent-traveler-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoff-ship%20excursions%20tend%20to%20cost%20extra%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20person%20can%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20spend%20a%20week%20on%20board%20without%20spending%20another%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20is%20why%2C%20for%20millions%20of%20repeat%20customers%2C%20cruising%20is%20the%20best%20and%20only%20way%20to%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20on%20a%20giant%20floating%20resort%20will%20never%20be%20for%20everyone.%20For%20the%20writer%20David%20Foster%20Wallace%2C%20in%20his%20famous%201991%20essay%20for%20Harper's%2C%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20about%20a%20mass-market%20Luxury%20Cruise%20that's%20unbearably%20sad.%26quot%3B%20Three%20decades%20later%2C%20many%20of%20the%20characteristics%20that%20ensure%20cruising's%20popularity%20and%20profitability%20are%20the%20same%20ones%20that%20burden%20it%20with%20ethical%20ballast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20cruise%20industry%20is%20dominated%20by%20the%20company%20Arison%20founded%2C%20Carnival%2C%20which%20owns%20almost%20half%20the%20entire%20global%20market%2C%20and%20Royal%20Caribbean%2C%20of%20which%20the%20Icon%20of%20the%20Seas%20is%20the%20latest%20flagship.%20Both%20companies%20are%20headquartered%20in%20Miami%2C%20but%20their%20vessels%20sail%20under%20what's%20known%20in%20maritime%20parlance%20as%20%26quot%3Bflags%20of%20convenience.%26quot%3B%20To%20bypass%20strict%20American%20regulations%20and%20high%20taxes%2C%20companies%20register%20their%20ships%20to%20a%20foreign%20country.%20Carnival%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20flagged%20to%20Panama%2C%20Royal%20Caribbean%20to%20the%20Bahamas.%20Originally%20pioneered%20by%20passenger-ship%20companies%20seeking%20to%20sell%20booze%20during%20Prohibition%2C%20today%20this%20tactic%20has%20enabled%20cruise%20lines%20to%20sidestep%20stringent%20labor%20laws.%20Low-ranking%20employees%20on%20large%20cruise%20ships%2C%20often%20from%20low-income%20countries%2C%20have%20reported%20working%20long%20hours%20for%20below%20minimum%20wage%2C%20while%20enjoying%20few%2C%20if%20any%2C%20employment%20benefits.%20(One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-ship-job-long-hours-low-pay-no-days-off-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eformer%20cruise%20worker%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20knew%20of%20colleagues%20working%20for%20as%20little%20as%20%242%20an%20hour.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20perhaps%20greater%20contention%20is%20the%20industry's%20immense%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarnivals-history-of-environmental-violations-cruise-industry-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenvironmental%20impact%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20common%20with%20most%20large%20oceangoing%20vessels%2C%20cruise%20ships%20have%20traditionally%20been%20powered%20by%20heavy%20fuel%20oil%2C%20a%20viscous%20diesel%20that%20tends%20to%20be%20the%20cheapest%20%E2%80%94%20read%3A%20dirtiest%20%E2%80%94%20fuel%20available.%20When%20burned%2C%20it%20emits%20prodigious%20quantities%20of%20CO2%2C%20as%20well%20as%20toxic%20particulates%20that%20contaminate%20the%20air%20and%20water.%20A%202019%20study%20by%20Transport%20%26amp%3B%20Environment%2C%20a%20Brussels%20nongovernmental%20organization%2C%20found%20that%20Carnival's%20European%20fleet%20emitted%2010%20times%20as%20much%20sulfur%20oxide%2C%20a%20pollutant%20that%20has%20been%20proved%20to%20harm%20the%20human%20respiratory%20system%2C%20as%20all%20the%20continent's%20260%20million%20passenger%20vehicles%20combined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Carnival%20Jubilee%20is%20transported%20by%20tugboat%20while%20a%20crowd%20watches%20from%20the%20grassy%20shore.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b13581617029e90a5ff9ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20new%20Carnival%20cruise%20ship%20is%20transported%20to%20The%20Netherlands.%3Cp%3ESarah%20Knorr%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECruise%20lines%20insist%20that%20a%20greener%20future%20is%20viable.%20Carnival%20has%20committed%20to%20halve%20its%20carbon%20emissions%20by%202030%20and%20reach%20net%20zero%20by%202050.%20Royal%20Caribbean%20promises%20a%20net-zero%20ship%20by%202035.%20But%20many%20climate%20experts%20say%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Btransitional%26quot%3B%20mitigations%20are%20nowhere%20near%20adequate.%20Liquefied%20natural%20gas%2C%20which%20powers%20most%20new%20cruise%20ships%2C%20including%20the%2090%2C000-horsepower%20engines%20on%20the%20Icon%2C%20emits%20about%2025%25%20less%20CO2%20than%20conventional%20marine%20fuels%2C%20but%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheicct.org%2Fpublication%2Fthe-climate-implications-of-using-lng-as-a-marine-fuel%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egenerates%20methane%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20particularly%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriends%20of%20the%20Earth's%20latest%20Cruise%20Ship%20Report%20Card%2C%20which%20scores%20major%20lines%20on%20metrics%20including%20air-pollution%20reduction%2C%20water-quality%20compliance%2C%20and%20transparency%2C%20gave%20both%20Carnival%20and%20Royal%20Caribbean%20yet%20another%20F.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCruise-ship%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20grew%20more%20than%2020%25%20between%202012%20and%202018%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20Comer%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Council%20on%20Clean%20Transportation's%20marine%20program%2C%20told%20me.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20bring%20that%20down%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20through%20%26quot%3Bmandatory%2C%20enforceable%20regulations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20anti-cruise%20activists%2C%20the%20wider%20climate%20crisis%20has%20become%20a%20rallying%20point.%20In%20October%2C%20when%20the%20World%20Traveller%2C%20a%20luxury%20cruise%20ship%20often%20assigned%20to%20the%20polar%20regions%2C%20arrived%20in%20the%20French%20port%20of%20Douarnenez%2C%20it%20was%20booed%20by%20a%20crowd%20of%20protesters%2C%20some%20dressed%20as%20walruses%20and%20polar%20bears.%20Anti-cruise%20sentiment%20has%20begun%20to%20carry%20over%20into%20restrictive%20legislation.%20Several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-us-port-towns-want-to-limit-ban-cruise-ships-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emajor%20cruise%20ports%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Venice%2C%20Italy%3B%20Dubrovnik%2C%20Croatia%3B%20and%20Amsterdam%2C%20have%20introduced%20prohibitions%20and%20levied%20new%20taxes%20on%20passengers.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20campaigners%20remain%20unsatisfied.%20%26quot%3BThe%20big%20cruise%20companies%20are%20playing%20three-dimensional%20chess%2C%20while%20the%20local%20governments%20play%20checkers%2C%26quot%3B%20Karla%20Hart%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Global%20Cruise%20Activist%20Network%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHart%2C%20whose%20hometown%20of%20Juneau%2C%20Alaska%2C%20is%20a%20summer%20cruise%20hub%2C%20said%20the%20industry%20had%20an%20ignominious%20history%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffoe.org%2Fcruise-history-violations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenvironmental%20violations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20of%20leveraging%20flags%20of%20convenience%2C%20clever%20marketing%2C%20and%20political%20clout%20to%20get%20its%20way.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20good%20at%20spinning%20the%20story%20to%20make%20themselves%20look%20better.%20But%20greenwashing%20and%20obfuscation%20are%20ingrained%20in%20the%20corporate%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20notoriety%2C%20boats%20such%20as%20the%20Icon%20are%20few%20in%20number.%20Cruise%20Market%20Watch%20forecasts%20there%20will%20be%20360%20cruise%20ships%20in%20service%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%2C%20comprising%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20global%20commercial%20fleet.%20But%20they're%20a%20conspicuous%20target.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20easy%20to%20point%20a%20finger%20at%20the%20ship%20in%20the%20harbor%20and%20say%20there's%20our%20problem.%20It's%20a%20lot%20harder%20to%20get%20angry%20about%20the%2037%20flights%20a%20day%20that%20are%20arriving%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%2C%20the%20cruise%20critic%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20port%20residents%20decry%20the%20ships'%20disruptive%20impact%2C%20others%20vaunt%20them%20as%20economically%20indispensable.%20In%20April%2C%20when%20ships%20returned%20to%20Skagway%2C%20Alaska%2C%20after%20a%20long%20COVID-19%20hiatus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcanada%2Fnorth%2Fskagway-alaska-tourists-season-1.6818337%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereports%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%20store%20owners%20weeping%20with%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20ongoing%20calls%20for%20ships%20to%20be%20proscribed%20risk%20precipitating%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20in%20which%20cruise%20companies%2C%20ostracized%20at%20traditional%20ports%2C%20merely%20reroute%20to%20their%20coastal%20concessions.%20Both%20of%20the%20routes%20traveled%20by%20the%20Icon%20of%20the%20Seas%20include%20a%20stop%20off%20at%20Royal%20Caribbean's%20private%20island%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperfect-day-cococay-private-bahamian-island-tour-photos-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPerfect%20Day%20at%20CocoCay%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20Bahamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20discourse%20boils%20down%20to%20cruise%20ships'%20arresting%20optics.%20The%20industry's%20tendency%20toward%20gigantism%20is%20partly%20about%20economies%20of%20scale%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20more%20cost-effective%20to%20squeeze%20as%20many%20passengers%20as%20possible%20onto%20one%20large%20ship%20than%20many%20small%20ships%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20also%20an%20arms%20race%20designed%20to%20polarize%20and%20provoke.%20%26quot%3BThat%20stern%20is%20such%20a%20departure%20from%20anything%20that%20has%20ever%20been%20created%20on%20a%20ship%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Icon's%20eye-catching%20rear%20end.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20always%20going%20to%20stir%20the%20pot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rendering%20of%20the%20Icon%20of%20the%20Seas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536d18496908fd7cdb582f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Icon%20of%20the%20Seas%20%26quot%3Bwas%20always%20going%20to%20stir%20the%20pot%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%3Cp%3ERoyal%20Caribbean%20International%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20detractors%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20each%20new%20incarnation%20of%20megaship%20seems%20to%20aspire%20to%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adding%20entr%C3%A9es%20to%20an%20already%20stuffed%20menu%2C%20can%20seem%20symbolic%20of%20an%20impatient%2C%20gluttonous%2C%20and%20superficial%20age%20%E2%80%94%20the%20perfect%20holiday%20for%20a%20society%20that%20demands%20constant%20diversion.%20%26quot%3BCruise%20passengers%20learn%20to%20be%20suspicious%20of%20anything%20outside%20of%20their%20cruise%20bubble.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20anything%20that's%20ugly.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20anything%20that's%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20Hart%20said.%20Her%20house%20often%20shakes%20from%20helicopter%20excursions%20carrying%20cruise%20passengers%20to%20Juneau's%20shrinking%20ice%20fields.%20%26quot%3BThese%20trips%20are%20sold%20as%20'once%20in%20a%20lifetime'%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it's%20basically%20a%20theme-park%20experience%20offered%20by%20companies%20that%20are%20trying%20to%20empty%20your%20wallet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20same%20resort-style%20product%20that%20repels%20some%20people%20proves%20irresistible%20to%20others%2C%20for%20whom%20a%20boat%20like%20the%20Icon%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20fantasy.%20While%20overseas%20travel%20has%20become%20freighted%20with%20anxiety%20post-pandemic%2C%20a%20cruise%20ship%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20is%20the%20ultimate%20contained%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20convenient%2C%20predictable%2C%20and%20hassle-free.%20From%20the%20moment%20of%20boarding%2C%20a%20passenger%20is%20insulated%20from%20the%20variables%20and%20complexities%20of%20traveling%20in%20a%20foreign%20place.%20The%20food%20and%20drink%20are%20always%20flowing.%20Your%20luggage%20is%20never%20far%20away.%20The%20entertainment%20runs%2024%2F7.%20Adrift%20on%20a%20parallel%20world%20of%20rest%20and%20recreation%2C%20the%20ships%20take%20you%20away%20from%20terrestrial%20concerns%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20away%20from%20moral%20scruples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20cruising%20is%20an%20industry%20that%20has%20long%20benefited%20from%20loopholes%20in%20maritime%20law%2C%20then%20today%20it%20also%20benefits%20from%20something%20else%3A%20a%20loophole%20in%20consumer%20conscience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fhenry-wismayer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHenry%20Wismayer%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20writer%20based%20in%20London.%20He%20writes%20essays%2C%20features%20and%20commentary%20for%20a%20range%20of%20publications%20including%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20National%20Geographic%2C%20Financial%20Times%2C%20and%20Noema.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-americans-love-cruises-icon-of-the-seas-gen-z-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E