ntent%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25121330%2Fdiana-polekhina-ZBstHWt9vLc-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EEven%20though%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1995855%5C%22%3Edismissed%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20single-dose%20human%3Cbr%3E%5Cnpapillomavirus%20(HPV)%20vaccination%20against%20cervical%20cancer%20would%20be%20included%20in%20the%20routine%20immunisation%20programme%2C%20a%20new%20study%20conducted%20at%20hospitals%20across%20India%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20one%20dose%20of%20the%20vaccine%20can%20prevent%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHPV%20is%20a%20sexually-transmitted%20infection%20that%20is%20responsible%20for%20almost%20all%20cases%20of%20cervical%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20conducted%20on%202%2C135%20women%20over%2010%20years%2C%20divided%20into%20groups%20who%20received%20one%2C%20two%20or%20three%3Cbr%3E%5Cndoses%20of%20HPV%20vaccines%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2010%20and%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20study%2C%20conducted%20at%20hospitals%20across%20India%2C%20found%20that%2010%20years%20after%20vaccination%2C%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20single-%20dose%20recipients%20still%20had%20antibody%20titers%20against%20HPV%20types%2016%20and%2018%20with%20the%20proportion%20being%20slightly%20higher%20among%2010-14-year-olds%20than%20those%20aged%2015-18%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fsingledose-hpv-jab-is-enough-to-prevent-cervical-cancer-indian-study-finds-11706118127728.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELivemint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%2C%20quoting%20the%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Cem%3EHuman%20Vaccines%20and%20Immunotherapeutics%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20this%20year%2C%20there%20were%20reports%20in%20the%20media%20saying%20that%20the%20HPV%20vaccine%20was%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20vaccine%20programme%2C%20targeting%20girls%20aged%209-14.%20However%2C%20the%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%20has%20since%20clarified%20that%20no%20such%20decision%20has%20been%20taken%20yet.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Union%20Health%20Ministry%20is%20yet%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20roll%20out%20of%20HPV%20vaccination%20in%20the%20country.%20It%20is%20closely%20monitoring%20the%20incidences%20of%20cervical%20cancer%20cases%20in%20the%20country%20and%20is%20in%20regular%20touch%20with%20states%20and%20various%20health%20departments%20regarding%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20PIB%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20research%2C%20%3Cem%3ELivemint%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%2C%20was%20carried%20out%20%E2%80%9Cto%20study%20the%20long-term%20antibody%20response%20after%20a%20single%20dose%20of%20the%20HPV%20vaccine%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20study%20showed%20that%20a%20single%20dose%20jab%20with%20a%20catch-up%20extended%20to%20age%2020%20will%20have%20more%20significant%20impact%20in%20reducing%20the%20lifetime%20risk%20of%20cervical%20cancer%20and%20accelerating%20elimination%20of%20the%20disease%20than%20administering%20two%20doses%20to%20pre-adolescent%20girls.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECervical%20cancer%20is%20the%20second%20most%20prevalent%20form%20of%20cancer%20among%20Indian%20women%2C%20after%20breast%20cancer.%20Across%20the%20world%2C%20the%20HPV%20vaccine%20has%20been%20recognised%20as%20an%20important%20preventive%20measure.%20The%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20has%20recommended%20that%20girls%20aged%20between%209%20and%2014%20should%20be%20given%20one%20or%20two%20HPV%20doses.%20A%20recent%20study%20in%20Scotland%20found%20that%20there%20were%20no%20cases%20of%20cervical%20cancer%20among%20women%20who%20received%20the%20full%20HPV%20immunisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc19132k8ke0o%5C%22%3EBBC%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706165052000%2C%22visual%22%3A%